11.16.22  9:28 pm   hey, bill! here's a few questions a got from the "out to lunch" video.

1. why is the dude going out to lunch when the clock says 2:55?

      (also 2:55 A.M. or P.M.?)

     2. what is he humming when he walks in the kitchen?

     a song (maybe one of yours, bill?) or just a random tune or something?

     3. what is he placing in the door handle of the kitchen cabinet/cupboard?

     4. are his ceiling tiles faulty or do they fall out easily when they're hit w/ something?

     5. who's calvin?

     6. is the going-out-to-lunch-guy's name "dan smith"?

     7. is he single, given the "looking for love? join a club" poster?

     8. are his juggling clubs somehow defying the laws of physics?

     and how the heck were they able to balance themselves on top of those light fixtures? (like dangm that's impressive.)

     9. how come there's like a gzbijhfillion electric sockets in the dude's house?

     10.  why does the fire extinguisher say "Water" on it?

      because the fire extinguisher foam that sprays out the fire extinguishers is essentially just water to put out fires? is there water in the fire extinguisher?

     and yes i know there's a lot of questions, and i ask a lot of questions, but i hope you don't mind. just felt curious about some of those things that I found/noticed in the video. thanks, bill!
